<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_ab69a8f2-99a3-4d74-9a9f-c65f13687a28" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>10.8.4</sptc><title id="_4cf8117a-e5c6-4947-ab4f-c56dc77139ec">Ventilation of a roof space with the primary insulation layer parallel to the roof plane</title><archive-num/><subclause id="_0a7d27f1-f671-4a9a-8bc9-498a94fc50ae" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b80a1052-0cad-4144-aca5-4917160a8d32">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>In <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_45195e00-beb5-44ff-beb1-53210517e142" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zones</xref> 6, 7 and 8, a roof system with the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/7180_0.6.0.xml#_e0128ee3-46f3-45d2-9b1b-e069b935fd58" id="_3322f2c1-160e-469d-b58a-9dcf7e5ea676" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">primary insulation layer</xref> installed parallel to the roof plane must have a roof space that—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_a7cb2a57-34ba-4553-82eb-41b6def0d9de">is located immediately above—<ol><li>the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/7180_0.6.0.xml#_e0128ee3-46f3-45d2-9b1b-e069b935fd58" id="_7bac07c4-80e4-41dc-add9-5f34c727e103" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">primary insulation layer</xref>; or</li><li>any <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10130_0.7.0.xml#_e53cf170-3a1e-49b9-942d-76571f407ccc" id="_12f495f4-aaa1-43a7-ba2b-b6be67e32697" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">control layer</xref> installed immediately above the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/7180_0.6.0.xml#_e0128ee3-46f3-45d2-9b1b-e069b935fd58" id="_5141af3a-446c-40db-88ed-f9a7d06655a9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">primary insulation layer</xref>; and</li></ol></li><li id="_fc260bc4-0cb1-4a56-a1ab-2c1be52b3bc7">is not obstructed by insulation; and</li><li id="_ec9f7d57-000f-41a5-ae69-36be3bd04897">has a height not less than 18 mm as measured perpendicular to the plane of the roof; and</li><li id="_cccf71ce-63ee-4578-81ec-eea73babb041">for roofs less than 10 m<sup id="_22e71c10-e17a-4778-bb54-ebb2d8cf935a">2</sup>, is ventilated to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1388_0.4.0.xml#_411d1010-9a7f-494c-af78-cf1ba1523530" id="_8c1ac410-f004-478e-8778-d67142129b11" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">outdoor air</xref> through openings not less than—<ol><li>7,000 mm<sup id="_c6709fc2-24f3-49b1-8e65-d5c934772039">2</sup>/m provided at the eaves or low level; and </li><li>5,000 mm<sup id="_1df6ab8e-224f-4131-8cd0-433b396237cc">2</sup>/m at the high level or ridge; and</li></ol></li><li id="_4aec4423-8bf9-4f3a-81ec-f4e125a604e1">for all other roofs, is ventilated to <xref format="dita" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:outdoor-air.xml#_eb74131f-b9dc-42bf-89c2-f68b788f9636" id="_f893a98b-4886-47c5-ab66-e04285f0ae93" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">outdoor air</xref> through openings not less than—<ol><li>20,000 mm<sup id="_069f31f7-690d-4a1b-8d0f-635dd1cb45b4">2</sup>/m provided at the eaves or low level; and</li><li>5,000 mm<sup id="_e54333fe-0a02-4f49-9d13-923a4ce55665">2</sup>/m at the high level or ridge.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_de7d6c3c-b421-4b47-b639-6bf9acab316f" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_44f56de2-f4c8-43c2-8858-ad7fb0ed0d98">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10130_0.7.0.xml#_e53cf170-3a1e-49b9-942d-76571f407ccc" id="_0c9089fd-dd82-4ad4-93f8-390820007d1d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">control layer</xref> is installed immediately above the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/7180_0.6.0.xml#_e0128ee3-46f3-45d2-9b1b-e069b935fd58" id="_1ea7dc38-97cc-4f3a-b814-0cf1814e6e36" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">primary insulation layer</xref> in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_441b649e-2a1d-404e-bc69-cd470ac32f41" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zones</xref> 6, 7 and 8, it must have a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/6175_0.10.0.xml#_6865163b-ba99-4d48-9e9b-a76b4641be1c" id="_77b01dd9-df83-48f2-8685-3858347f6648" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">vapour permeance</xref> of not less than 1.14 μg/N.s.</p></subclause><subclause id="_f9d04da1-35de-4511-a39e-fcd3736b559d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c918fb7b-d90b-49a3-be8a-1c4e59717812">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>The requirements of (1) do not apply to a—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_7aaaa496-e79f-4e49-b40d-cbbad76c6901">concrete roof; or</li><li id="_4fe06b28-1bd1-4e12-a5c4-55fdd0e92c6c">roof that is made of insulated sandwich panels with or without an additional ceiling lining; or</li><li id="_49f0fd88-3fe1-49c0-aec2-13a4ffff5b06">roof that is subject to Bushfire Attack Level FZ requirements in accordance with AS 3959; or</li><li id="_e882d5d3-e288-4b04-a2cb-4dfbe8bfe0a6">tiled roof without a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10130_0.7.0.xml#_e53cf170-3a1e-49b9-942d-76571f407ccc" id="_5cd11878-a207-4795-9cdd-88963bfaba59" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">control layer</xref> located above the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/7180_0.6.0.xml#_e0128ee3-46f3-45d2-9b1b-e069b935fd58" id="_163036af-68d9-47be-bbb2-811e204beeca" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">primary insulation layer</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_c51acc0b-48c1-4968-90c7-b0c9f2daba5f"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><title id="_28dfcf88-bddd-4868-9fc9-d356796fcba7">Explanatory Information</title><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10125_0.12.0.xml#_4a5ed6f6-7d55-48d0-a43d-573983150d1a" id="_724b59da-8c81-4a1c-981b-eb86d4813fd4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Explanatory Figure 10.8.4a</xref> is an example of when a roof comprises of one roof space with multiple roof types, combining requirements for Part <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/2039_1.47.0.xml#_c4feece9-e6aa-4e96-84b1-751f352f799a" id="_a525325a-e713-44fa-b8eb-9180351216b1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">10.8.3</xref> and 10.8.4. In this instance the low level ventilation requirements for each roof type are applicable, however, only one high level opening is required at the ridge as the lower roof opening is discharging into the larger roof space.</p><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10127_0.10.0.xml#_c9ecc787-2106-4b21-943d-b80b9382ec2b" id="_95c9ab06-237b-419e-9fcc-de99ccc6e2c6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Explanatory Figure 10.8.4b</xref> is an example of a roof type complying with 10.8.4(1)(a)(i), where the roof space is above the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/7180_0.6.0.xml#_e0128ee3-46f3-45d2-9b1b-e069b935fd58" id="_1c3081c9-a72a-43e7-9a62-0db041dda655" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">primary insulation layer</xref>. </p><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10129_0.10.0.xml#_38681e21-dcce-4251-8508-34720e907f63" id="_fbc6a1cd-d147-483e-aee9-5dc67ec58cc7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Explanatory Figure 10.8.4c</xref> is an example of a roof type complying with 10.8.4(1)(a)(ii), where the roof space is above the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10130_0.7.0.xml#_bf941671-62c3-4828-a166-194df81df7d6" id="_0ebcb738-cdbb-4e56-8867-7f54d8db7899" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">control layer</xref> installed immediately above the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/7180_0.6.0.xml#_e0128ee3-46f3-45d2-9b1b-e069b935fd58" id="_bf445129-ff4f-4f2c-a87b-b1f33c376693" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">primary insulation layer</xref>. </p><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10125_0.12.0.xml" id="_4a5ed6f6-7d55-48d0-a43d-573983150d1a"><num/><title id="_b0596102-42c7-48b3-8750-f7e58926e3f2"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10127_0.10.0.xml" id="_c9ecc787-2106-4b21-943d-b80b9382ec2b"><num/><title id="_51e82a12-6423-45cb-b1c7-0d5f2e06020f"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/10129_0.10.0.xml" id="_38681e21-dcce-4251-8508-34720e907f63"><num/><title id="_24a8c764-20c0-4099-8dbc-2518683f0fa4"/></image-reference></callout></clause>